RACE.FOOTNOTES: INVINCIBLE cleared from inside, showed the way through the turn, drew away when asked and was ridden out to the wire. UNCHARTED raced in mid-pack outside a rival, three deep at the quarter pole, moved out and rallied in the final furlong and bested the rest. AMERICAN HOPE got bumped and put in tight early, raced inside a pair of rivals towards the rear leaving the backstretch, tipped out at the top of the stretch but lacked room behind rivals, gained a clear path and kept on but got outfinished for the place honors. EL REY REY was off slow to begin, trailed two wide into the turn, lacked room around the bend, looked to gain a clear path but had to steady when lacking room in upper stretch, altered out at the eighth pole and put in a late run. STICK SHIFT stalked from inside, saved ground through the turn and flattened in deep stretch. EIGHT CLAP was off slow to begin, settled inside, got boxed past the three-eighths pole, shifted two wide near the quarter pole, lugged inward in upper stretch and could not rally in the furlong grounds. GOLD FOOT stalked up close in the two path into the turn, drifted in upper stretch and weakened. SHEAR MAGIC bumped with inner rival and got crowded early, chased between foes into the turn in the two path, tipped three wide into the lane and failed to menace. CITADINO traveled three deep near the back, came four wide into the lane and failed to make an impact. SIR MAXIMUS chased under coaxing up the backstretch off the rail then between rivals, lost ground on the turn, got crowded at the quarter pole and faded. TEDDY'S TRIUMPH chased two wide into the turn, angled to the rail at the quarter pole bothered by GOLD FOOT drifting over in upper stretch and weakened.

CASIA hit the gate to lose a step at the start, stalked between rivals, brushed with IIA VEIW TOO entering the turn three wide, remained in that path to the stretch and finished evenly late. ILA VEIW TOO broke a step slow, stalked outside the leader up the backstretch, brushed with CASIA entering the turn, rounded the bend two wide and lacked a bid in the final furlong. OAK CREEK GAL was off a bit slow to begin, went up to chase up close four deep, dropped back around the turn, angled in exiting the bend and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MADISON RAE broke well, stalked from inside then switch outside the pacesetter, bid between foes around the bend, fought three wide into the lane, battled down the stretch and edged MISS MICHE LADA late. MISS MICHE LADA cleared and steered across to the inside, met bids from outer rivals around the bend, held a short lead two wide into the stretch, fought with MADISON RAE through the lane and yielded grudgingly. PURA VIDA stalked the pace from inside, cut the corner into the lane, failed to find the needed late kick to challenge the top pair but outfinished HOT DANZING for the show. HOT DANZING stalked up close from outside, bid three deep on the turn, could not kick on with the leaders entering the final furlong and flattened to fourth. STAY ZAPPY settled off the pace, ridden along on the turn, shifted ground at the quarter pole and failed to threaten in the final furlong. SIGNORA VITTORIA dropped back early then moved up outside the leaders four deep, failed to sustain the bid around the turn, chased three wide into the lane and weakened. MEMORYSINTHEPARK chased widest up the backstretch, went five wide into the turn, dropped back around the bend, trailed three wide into the lane and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 96. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUCINO pressed four then three wide between rivals around the first turn, headed the leader with three furlongs remaining, took over three deep at the five-sixteenths pole, dueled with BAD SNEAKERS into the stretch, lost command in upper stretch, fought back in the final furlong and was all out to edge the runner-up. BAD SNEAKERS stalked two wide then moved inside on the first turn, launched a bid inside the top pair at the five-sixteenths pole, put a head in front in upper stretch, battled MUCINO into deep stretch and finished gamely in defeat. MIXTO rated on the inside then moved out around the first turn, chased two then three wide on the second bend, angled out in upper stretch and gained the show. BRING HIM HOME trailed on the inside, altered around rival leaving the far turn and could not rally. THRUST vied inside a pair of rivals three wide into the first turn then moved into the two path while taking command, set the pace under pressure up the backstretch, headed near the three-eighths pole, overtaken while between rivals at the five-sixteenths pole, started to weaken with a quarter mile remaining, tired and eased in the lane and walked off.

All horses to pay $1,500 to enter and an additional $1,500 to start with $200,000 gu aranteed of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at One Mile Or Over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of A race other than Claiming or Starter at One Mile or Over allowed 4 lbs. Maidens 6 lbs. High weights preferred, Stakes winners second preference and third preference to Stakes placed horses. Total earnings in races other than claiming or starter will be used to determine preference of horses of equal we ight. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENDLESSLY traveled in mid-pack outside a rival, angled in on the far turn while moving into range, tipped out to take aim at NGANNOU in upper stretch, drew alongside that rival past the eighth pole and drove clear. NGANNOU dueled from inside into the first turn then took control around the bend, led under mild pressure from outer rivals up the backstretch, cleared approaching the quarter pole, challenged by ENDLESSLY inside the eighth pole, lost command nearing the sixteenth pole and stayed on to secure second. GRAND MO THE FIRST was off a bit slow to begin, trailed into the first turn on the inside, went outside a pair of rivals into the far turn, was on the move three then four wide around that bend, chased within striking distance with a furlong remaining but finished evenly late. ACE OF CLUBS traveled two wide near the back early on then outside a rival, asked right handed past the quarter pole, angled to the inside in upper stretch, kept on through the final furlong but got edged for the show. MICI'S EXPRESS settled inside, got blocked nearing the five-sixteenths pole, tipped two wide into the clear and passed tired rivals. FORMIDABLE MAN dueled from outside into the first turn then chased the leader around the bend, moved up to apply pressure from between in the middle stages, lost touch with the NGANNOU approaching the quarter pole, chased two wide into the lane, bothered by the winner coming out and had to steady outside the eighth pole and was not persevered with after. BOLTAGE raced up close three deep, failed to kick on with the pacesetter with a quarter mile remaining, remained three wide into the stretch and weakened. POUR DOMPTER (FR) broke a step slow, stalked on the inside then in mid-pack on the backstretch, dropped back on the far turn and had little left for the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOST OF MIDNIGHT got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, stalked in hand early, bid between into the turn, inched ahead then cleared past the quarter pole, drifted out a bit under left handed urging and powered away in the lane. MIDNIGHT FURY broke out and bumped, dueled for command outside a rival up the backstretch, vied three deep around the bend, could not kick on with GHOST OF MIDNIGHT past the quarter pole and stayed on through the drive to best the rest. PRINCIP got put in tight between foes early, chased five deep into the turn, four deep into the lane and got outfinished for the place honors. TIZ TOK dueled for command from inside, vied with outer pair into the turn, lost touch with the winner with a quarter mile remaining, remained inside and got put in tight in upper stretch, then faded in the furlong grounds. Total earnings in races other than claiming or starter will be used to determine preference of horses of equal weight. Atr ophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMFYRE set the pace on the inside under pressure, met a pair of bids from outside at the five-sixteenths pole, inched ahead in upper stretch, drifted out and bumped BUTTERCREAM BABE late and gamely prevailed. BUTTERCREAM BABE pressed from outside to the far turn, vied between rivals around the bend, fought outside DREAMFYRE into the final furlong, got bumped by that rival past the sixteenth pole and could not get by. FLATTERY stalked along the inside, roused midway around the far turn, stayed along the rail into the stretch and showed a mild rally to gain the show honors. WHERE'S MY RING bobbled shortly after the start, was taken back and started to pull early, continued to tug up the backstretch and onto the three-eighths pole, let loose around the second bend, moved out in upper stretch and kept on for a minor award. SOHO pulled early, raced in range in the two path, launched a bid three deep at the five-sixteenths pole, could not go on with the leaders entering the final furlong and flattened in deep stretch. ZONA VERDE (IRE) was fractious in the gate, broke a bit slow, trailed on the inside into the clubhouse turn, tipped two wide second bend, moved out in upper stretch, then steered back in and improved position. ANGIOLLETA (IRE) broke a step slow, settled outside a rival, drew closer two wide on the far turn and lacked a rally. PUTT FOR DOUGH settled inside, looked to split rivals but lacked room and had to check at the five-sixteenths pole, chased along the inside into the stretch and was not persevered with late. SUSHI STICKS reserved early and tucked inside near the back, steadied when running up on rivals heels into the far turn, got blocked around that bend and failed to threaten. THE RIDER ABOARD BUTTERCREAM BABE LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST DREAMFYRE FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE LATE IN THE STRETCH AND THERE WAS ALSO A STEWARDS INQUIRY INTO THE SAME INCIDENT. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT ALTHOUG DREAMFYRE DID DRIFT OUT AND MAKE CONTACT WITH BUTTERCREAM BABE LATE, THE INCIDENT DID NOT WARRANT A DISQUALIFICATION.
